    Install Cinnamon
    *****************
        ...Cinnamon is a Gnome 3 fork that allow you to have a panel at the bottom with a classic Menu, this is useful for people that want to use Ubuntu with a classic Bottom Menu.
        sudo add-apt-repository ppa:gwendal-lebihan-dev/cinnamon-stable
        sudo apt-get update
        sudo apt-get install cinnamon
        
    Installing Medibuntu
    *********************
        ...Medibuntu is a packaging project dedicated to distributing software that cannot be included in Ubuntu for various reasons, related to geographical variations in      legislationMedibuntu regarding intellectual property, security and other issues. by adding Medibuntu repositories you will be able to install many softwares like Google-Earth , opera ,Win32codecs
        Copy paste this command > "sudo -E wget --output-document=/etc/apt/sources.list.d/medibuntu.list http://www.medibuntu.org/sources.list.d/$(lsb_release -cs).list && sudo apt-get --quiet update && sudo apt-get --yes --quiet --allow-unauthenticated install medibuntu-keyring && sudo apt-get --quiet update"
        ...if you want to add medibuntu packages to Ubuntu software center, 
        sudo apt-get install app-install-data-medibuntu apport-hooks-medibuntu
        
